Often when a particularly evil criminal is executed,

suspicious folk fear that the criminal's remains might

rise from death to continue to plague the living. To

combat this possibility, many mobs or rural justices take

to the practice of burning the bodies, grinding the bones,

and scattering the remains in the wild. Yet in the case of

particularly evil criminals, even these steps are in vain,

