prehensile tails and handlike feet capable of well-articulated

movements. A vanara stands slightly shorter than a typical

human. Males weigh from 150 to 200 pounds at most, with

females weighing slightly less. Vanaras live for 60 to 75 years.

Vanaras live in large, tree-top villages connected by

rope-bridges and ladders. Homes are carved out of trees

but usually left open to the elements except for woven leaf

canopies and overhangs. Vanara villages are typically led by

the community's religious leader-usually a cleric,

oracle, or monk.

